  {panel}

*Original description*

Add ability to bulk edit issue time tracking estimates.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-5018].
  {panel}

It would be really useful sometimes to be able to quickly add a version.

For example, sometimes I just want to create a new version given it's name - none of the other stuff. Sort of like creating a subtask quickly. Why can't we just put a form at the bottom of the versions page to quickly add a new version, which defaults to no due date and at the end of the list? 

It would be useful for quickly creating lots of versions too. If you want to manage, you can still do that.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-5014].
  {panel}

At the moment component assignees are only shown on a "special" component assignees page. A lot of users are not aware of that page.

The component assignees should be visible and editable on add/edit component pages.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-4997].
  {panel}

Switching workflows in a fairly large JIRA instance (10000) takes about 90 minutes on a 3Ghz box, with all issues cached and little disk activity.  We should do some profiling and find out why it takes so long.

I tried many ways to import issues by CSV import, but always the same problem:
Issues imported correctly, but Jira shows all statuses as 10-Novo (our <New> status); I was looking even in our Jira tables in MSSqlServer, statuses and wfsteps seems to match (of course we are using our own workflow). 

Can you explain me what exactly this map does?

        wfStatusMap.put("1", "Unassigned");
        wfStatusMap.put("2", "Assigned");
        wfStatusMap.put("3", "In Progress");
        wfStatusMap.put("4", "Reopened");
        wfStatusMap.put("5", "Resolved");
        wfStatusMap.put("6", "Closed");

And where can I find the right values (in this map) in our workflow?

LukaS

